<div class="page-header">
    <h2>Backup Scheduling</h2>
</div>
<p class="text-muted">
    To schedule automatic backups, configure a Windows Task Scheduler job that invokes your database backup script or calls this application's backup endpoint.
</p>
<ol>
    <li>Create a PowerShell script to call the BACKUP DATABASE command or an admin API endpoint.</li>
    <li>Open Task Scheduler, create a new task, set triggers (daily/weekly), and actions to run the script.</li>
    <li>Ensure the task has proper permissions and the destination folder exists.</li>
</ol>
<p>
    For SQL Server Express, see "sqlcmd" usage, or for LocalDB, consider detaching/copying the MDF/LDF offline.
</p>
